# A modular content architecture eliminates waste and accelerates channel coverage
@type: two_column

@col:
  ## Current State (Linear Production)
  - Brief → agency → one execution → one channel
  - Each piece created for a single format and audience
  - Asset library disorganized; teams re-create vs. re-use
  - Average production cycle: 6–8 weeks per campaign
  - Estimated waste: $38M in underutilized assets

@col:
  ## Future State (Modular Architecture)
  - Brief → core asset → automated variant generation
  - One content "molecule" produces 12–15 channel variants
  - Centralized DAM with taxonomy and search capability
  - Average production cycle: 2–3 weeks with 3× more outputs
  - Estimated saving: $22M redirectable to paid media

@notes: The investment in a digital asset management system is typically the bottleneck. Budget $3–5M for implementation plus integration with the existing marketing stack.

